    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1052"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1052">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/4–2845</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-28">April 28,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: It is the position of the
                    Department of State that the attached cable<note n="88" xml:id="d1052fn1">This
                        message became Fan 536; see footnotes 82, <ref target="#pg_1121">p.
                            1121</ref>, and 94, <ref target="#pg_1128">p. 1128</ref>.</note> to the
                    Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater, concerning the establishment of
                    military government in the Compartment of Venezia Giulia and other sections of
                        <pb facs="1138" n="1126" xml:id="pg_1126"/> Italian territory, should be
                    dispatched as a matter of great political urgency.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph</hi> C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
